# MCP Server

Uses `github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/mcp` (official SDK, v1.5+).

## Server Setup

```go
server := mcp.NewServer(
    &mcp.Implementation{Name: "laightdb", Version: "v0.1.0"},
    nil,
)
```

## Adding Tools

Tool handlers use typed input/output structs with json + jsonschema tags:

```go
type StoreInput struct {
    Collection  string            `json:"collection" jsonschema:"collection name"`
    Content     string            `json:"content" jsonschema:"the content to store"`
    ContentType string            `json:"content_type" jsonschema:"code, conversation, doc, or kv"`
    Metadata    map[string]string `json:"metadata,omitempty" jsonschema:"key-value metadata tags"`
}

mcp.AddTool(server, &mcp.Tool{
    Name:        "store_context",
    Description: "Store content in LaightDB with metadata",
}, handleStoreContext)

func handleStoreContext(ctx context.Context, req *mcp.CallToolRequest, input StoreInput) (
    *mcp.CallToolResult, any, error,
) {
    // call context store, return result
}
```

## Transports

**stdio** (subprocess mode):
```go
server.Run(ctx, &mcp.StdioTransport{})
```

**Streamable HTTP** (network mode):
```go
handler := mcp.NewStreamableHTTPHandler(
    func(r *http.Request) *mcp.Server { return server },
    nil,
)
http.Handle("/mcp", handler)
```

Select via CLI flag: `--transport=stdio|http`

## Tool List

| Tool | Description | Key Params |
|---|---|---|
| `store_context` | Store content | collection, content, content_type, metadata |
| `search_context` | Hybrid search | query, collection, filters, top_k, detail |
| `get_context` | Get by ID | id, detail (metadata/summary/full) |
| `delete_context` | Delete by ID | id |
| `list_collections` | List collections | -- |
| `get_stats` | Database statistics | -- |
| `link_context` | Create directed edge | from_id, to_id, label, weight, source |
| `unlink_context` | Delete edge | edge_id |
| `get_neighbors` | BFS neighbors | id, max_depth |
| `get_subtree` | Directed subtree | id, max_depth |
| `graph_search` | BM25 + vector + graph RRF | query, focus_node_id, max_depth, … |
| `suggest_links` | Vector link suggestions | id, threshold, top_k |

## Resources

Expose collections as browsable MCP resources. Each collection URI: `laightdb://collections/{name}`.

## Error Handling

Return `*mcp.CallToolResult` with `IsError: true` and text content describing the error. Never panic in tool handlers.
